cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of machine learning and predictive modelling in analysing cardiac electrophysiology data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of complex spatio-temporal information, which suggests the possibility of using computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of predictive modelling, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of deep learning approaches suggests the possibility of the paper falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
